{"TopicId":200019,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"How Do I Turn Off Steam Games Auto Update On My PC?","CreatedByName":"Boknapp","CreatedById":201717,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-02-02T12:04:00Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Boknapp","CreatedById":201717,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-02-02T12:04:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello friends. How can I disable auto updates on Steam? Whenever I am working, Steam auto updates all my games which eat up the entire bandwidth. This slows my internet to crawling speed. Any suggestions will be appreciated.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-02-02T12:05:08Z\u0022 title=\u002202/02/2021 12:05  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 2, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by Boknapp\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EFor grammar mistake\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Caerfinon","CreatedById":207619,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-02-02T12:11:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223918644\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022200019\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221612267440\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022201717\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Boknapp\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Boknapp said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny suggestions will be appreciated\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can limit download speeds and times in Steam settings\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Q5WieqA.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002278.85\u0022 height=\u0022589\u0022 width=\u0022747\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/Q5WieqA.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr you can go into \u003Cstrong\u003Eoffline mode\u003C/strong\u003E and the games will not update at all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-02-02T14:58:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI strongly recommend, after downloading the KSP version of your choice, to copy the respective directory to another location (e.g. C:\\KSP) and only play KSP from there. This way, amongst other issues, you\u0027ll avoid any \u0022surprise\u0022 updates. There\u0027s no need to have Steam running to play KSP.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jimmymcgoochie","CreatedById":199902,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-02-02T17:24:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/207619-caerfinon/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022207619\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/207619-caerfinon/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Caerfinon\u003C/a\u003Esaid, you can restrict download times and speeds (I didn\u0027t know that!), and/or\u00A0change the settings on a per-game basis to only update when you launch the game through Steam, meaning it will only download updates when you tell it to.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Boknapp","CreatedById":201717,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-02-03T05:34:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223918645\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022200019\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221612267894\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022207619\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Caerfinon\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 hours ago, Caerfinon said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can limit download speeds and times in Steam settings\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/Q5WieqA.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Q5WieqA.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002278.85\u0022 height=\u0022589\u0022 width=\u0022747\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/Q5WieqA.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr you can go into \u003Cstrong\u003Eoffline mode\u003C/strong\u003E and the games will not update at all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for replying and you are absolutely correct. However, I already found \u003Ca href=\u0022https://digicruncher.com/steam-to-disable-auto-update/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ethis\u003C/a\u003E and scheduled the game updates to non-working hours.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}